  <text id="R119285942T">
    <front id="d2">
      <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
        <p>Colonel Michael G. Harman, Confederate commander and quartermaster at Staunton, VA,
          discusses supplies captured at Winchester in September, 1862.</p>
      </div1>
    </front>
    <body id="d4">
      <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
        <head>
          <name type="recipient"> Gen. COOPER, Adjutant and Inspector Gen.:</name>
        </head>
        <opener>
          <dateline>
            <date value="1862-09-05">September 5, 1862.</date>
            <name type="place">STAUNTON, VA.,</name>
          </dateline>
          <salute>The following dispatch has just been received from Lieut.-Col. Funk:</salute>
        </opener>
        <p>I am in possession of Winchester, capturing some 90 prisoners, large amount of
          quartermaster's and commissary stores, ammunition, &amp;c. They blew up a large
          magazine and two blocks of houses, retreating to Martinsburg. Inquire of Confederate
          States marshal what I shall do in regard to the stock of goods the merchants have on hand.
          Please advise and answer immediately by telegraph, via Harrisonburg.<lb/> J. H. S.
          FUNK,<lb/> Lieut.-Col.</p>
        <p>I have sent A. Lynn to take charge of the goods. Please telegraph immediately what I
          shall do with them.</p>
        <closer>
          <salute>Very respectfully,</salute>
          <signed>M. G. HARMAN,<lb/> Col. Fifty-second Regt. Virginia Volunteers.</signed>
        </closer>
      </div1>
    </body>
  </text>
